            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Although neovim ships a copy of curl such that it can be assumed to exist on all major platforms, this is still less nice to work with than it could be. \n\nAddressed by `vim.net.request` https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/34140 . There is still followup work to do, but it works for the basics.\n\n> For instance, differing locales can make it harder to parse curl output\n\nWhat is an example response and use-case where locale would affect curl output? \n\n> Also, on Windows in particular, starting processes can be very slow, so if a plugin needs to download a lot of files, this can add up.\n\nStructured concurrency / `vim.async` would address that.",
